The paper proposes a novel data-driven Bayesian algorithm for reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm also involves exploration and optimization, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of prior information, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY) and mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
